      <scopecontent id="aspace_0ce02ae6e35a795c2a8ee3ede854e027">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>in the two decades following his military service in South Africa. A scrapbook collection of poetry by McCarthy and clippings of poetry by others is also included.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <bioghist id="aspace_fd2030331d763a8b30e7eb676eaf0c55">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Alfred Stephen McCarthy was born September 8, 1878, in Mudgee, New South Wales, Australia. From 1900-1901, he served in South Africa with the 6th Imperial Bushmen of the Imperial Bushmen's Contingent, an Australian cavalry unit. Following this period of service, he returned to New South Wales where he worked as a local police sergeant.</p>
         <p>ence in the Boer War and observations of contemporary life in Australia. Aside from the poetry, there is scant evidence of McCarthy's life for the period following his discharge from the police department until his death in 1955.</p>  
      </bioghist>
